        <h2 class="sm:text-3xl text-2xl title-font font-medium text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-4">Government prescribes tech diet to solve malnutrition and hunger problems</h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-8">India has fast-tracked the use of technology and data to solve its malnutrition problem and push itself higher on the global rankings. The country rose eight positions from last year on the Global Hunger Index, yet is ranked 94th out of 107 countries in terms of hunger, according to study released in December. </p>
